You can get the loop device tar file from tsx-11 without contravening any
laws, as in itself it doesn't contain any DES code. You have to still get the
des code separately if you want any encryption. Alternatively you can add
a non-U.s. encryption of you choice very eaisly.

Mitch

BTW The latest lo is lo.3.5a.tar.gz but hasn't been moved to tsx-11 
.../BETA/loop yet. You may get it from ftp.mrc-apu.cam.ac.uk /pub/linux
if you desire.
